</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="86.[313,1269,1383,1693]" box="[313,421,1383,1406]" pageId="86" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis box="[313,421,1383,1406]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="590">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="86.[313,1269,1383,1693]" lastBlockId="87.[313,1268,1573,1693]" lastPageId="87" lastPageNumber="591" pageId="86" pageNumber="590">
The combination of scutellum with anterior pair of small hairs (shorter and finer than those at rear of scutum) and posterior pair of bristles; mesopleuron with 13 short hairs; and costal index 0.43; will take this species to group 
<collectionCode box="[1071,1090,1478,1501]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="86" pageNumber="590" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
of Borgmeier’s (1967a) keys, to 
<taxonomicName authority="Bormeier. However" authorityName="Bormeier. However" box="[507,926,1510,1534]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turbidipennis">
<emphasis box="[507,691,1510,1534]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="590">M. turbidipennis</emphasis>
Bormeier. However
</taxonomicName>
, the near-dorsal hair palisade of the mid tibia extends only about two-thirds of length in this species, but to nearly three-quarters in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="DISNEY" authorityYear="2003" box="[507,625,1573,1597]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trudiae">
<emphasis box="[507,625,1573,1597]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="590">M. trudiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and its costal cilia are &lt;
<quantity box="[914,996,1574,1598]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="86" pageNumber="590" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
long, but 
<quantity box="[1111,1268,1574,1598]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="86" pageNumber="590" unit="mm" value="0.135" valueMax="0.14" valueMin="0.13">0.13–0.14 mm</quantity>
in 
<emphasis box="[342,469,1605,1629]" italics="true" pageId="86" pageNumber="590">
<taxonomicName authorityName="DISNEY" authorityYear="2003" box="[342,465,1605,1629]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="86" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trudiae">M. trudiae</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
If some specimens turn up with a costal index&gt;0.43 then they would run to group IV. The combination of a lack of differentiated anterodorsal hairs on hind tibia; yellow haltere knob; forked vein 3; four supra-antennal bristles; long costal cilia; and costal ratios of 3.6–3.7:1.6:1; will take this species to couplet 10 (p. 206), to 
<taxonomicName authority="Beyer. However" authorityName="Beyer. However" box="[455,812,1605,1630]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="agnatoides">
<emphasis box="[455,615,1605,1629]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="591">M. agnatoides</emphasis>
Beyer. However
</taxonomicName>
, the costal cilia of the latter are longer (
<quantity box="[321,407,1637,1661]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="87" pageNumber="591" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
) and its costal index is 0.5. Labella not enlarged and with few spinules below; both left and right lobes of hypandrium vestigial.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5273680" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5273680" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5273680/files/figure.png" pageId="87" pageNumber="591" startId="87.[313,329,1456,1477]" targetBox="[314,1267,137,1429]" targetPageId="87">
<paragraph blockId="87.[313,1268,1454,1504]" pageId="87" pageNumber="591">
F. 45. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[417,519,1455,1476]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="87" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[417,519,1455,1476]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="591">Megaselia</emphasis>
